2022 is almost over!! This was by far our very best year ever 🖤 The shop is busier and stronger than ever and I truly couldn’t be more grateful 🥹 

I feel that I’m at a good place in my career to start pushing my comfort zone and take on more custom projects again. 
I have been LOVING the freedom and challenge that comes with taking walkins, but missing the artistry associated with larger pieces. 

For 2023 I would like to start tattooing Japanese inspired pieces. I know this is also an area @yenn_ink is wanting to explore more too! 

I spent hours tweaking this design, because I struggle showing a completed tattoo design with digital art, BUT I am determined to keep working at it, because adding color to my tattoos is something I’d like to do more often and showing clients what’s in my head is important. 

If anyone is interested in helping me gain more experience with modern Japanese tattoos, I will be offering a big discount on the first 5 large scale tattoo ideas! 
Please call or text the shop if you are interested!! 
Think dragons, snakes, flowers, geishas, hannya or oni masks, omamori….💋
On arms, thighs, backs, anything BIG!!

Last tattoo of the year!! 2023 will be the year I learn to take a picture of color tattoos!! Maybe… I really don’t understand how to do it at all. I guess I need to buy $3000 of special equipment but I just don’t care because this shit looks 🔥 in real life!! Which is all that really matters ❤️
BEST YEAR EVER!! 2023 will be even better!

With a degree and a Master in philosophy, combined with a passion for art, @vacio.tattoo has created a space for collectors
to receive a tattoo experience that is not only aesthetically pleasing but also meaningful. Vacio believes that tattoos are a form of self-expression, a way to convey one’s beliefs, values, and experiences through art. She understands that every tattoo has a story behind it, and she takes the time to listen to her clients and understand what they want to express through their tattoo. Having lived in countries such as Colombia, Spain, France and Denmark, she’s open to listen to your ideas whether you speak English, Spanish or French.
If you’re looking for a tattoo experience that is more than just skin deep, Vacio Tattoo is the place to go. Contact Vacio today to start your journey to a surreal, meaningful and beautiful tattoo.
